text: Macrozamia elegans is a species of plant in the family Zamiaceae. It is endemic to New South Wales, Australia.Hill, K.D. 2010. Macrozamia elegans. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2015.2. Downloaded on 06 September 2015. This species grows in the Blue Mountains near the village of Mountain Lagoon. It occurs in dense vegetation in eucalypt woodland habitat. ==References== elegans Category:Endangered flora of Australia Category:Flora of New South Wales Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
